<title>FINLAND: WPP HEAD SEES ADVERTISING GROWTH DOWN IN 98 - PAPER.</title>
<headline>WPP HEAD SEES ADVERTISING GROWTH DOWN IN 98 - PAPER.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1997-05-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>World advertising growth will slow next year to 4-5 percent from an estimated 6-7 percent this year, Martin Sorrell, CEO of the world' largest advertising agency WPP Group, was quoted as saying on Monday.</p>
<p>Expansion would be strongest in South America and Asia with double-digit growth rates, Finnish business daily Kauppalehti quoted Sorrell as saying in an interview.</p>
<p>-- Helsinki Newsroom +358-0-680 50 292, news@reuters.fi</p>
